				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ K_{\mathrm{v}}\frac{\partial{N}}{\partial{t}}\left|{~}_{z = 0}=-\gamma(N-N^{*})\right. , $$\end{document}where N is a generic dissolved nutrient state variable, Kv is the turbulent vertical diffusion coefficient (m2/s), N∗ is the observed value and γ is an empirical relaxation velocity chosen to be 0.6 m/day. The chosen nudging surface boundary condition accounts for the external nutrient inputs from rivers.
